txt.en: Orchalwë has told you of a cruel practice of the Angmarim that have occupied the ruins of Annúminas: drowning their prisoners off the docks at the Port of Annúminas.

'The Angmarim are cruel beyond measure, [placeholder], drowning the prisoners they have taken off the docks of the Port of Annúminas. They take pleasure in the suffering of their victims and must be stopped! We must put an end to these barbaric acts!

'I beg of you, if you are a friend to the Dúnedain and to the people of this land, hurry and put an end to these practices!

'Such cruelty deserves to be repaid tenfold, [placeholder], but we must be content to free the prisoners from their cruelty. Would that we could devise even worse punishments for these servants of the Iron Crown!'
Prisoners are being drowned by Angmarim torturers off the docks of the Port of Annúminas, on the lowest level of the city, by the water.

'I thank you from the very bottom of my heart, [placeholder]. I am relieved that some of the prisoners, at least, were given freedom.\n\n'A day will come when Angmar will pay for the full extent of its crimes!'
Orchalwë will be pleased to hear that the prisoners have been saved.
'Save those prisoners, [placeholder], and dispatch the foul Angmarim.'
